nodes.bodyText:
There's no need for the @SuppressWarnings if you factor out
    static void addOption(List<String> options, String option, String value) {
        if (value != null) options.add(String.format("%s=\"%s\"", option, value));
    }
Which works for all the String-valued options. For the boolean ones, is there anything to be gained by only adding the option when the value is true/false, or would it work as well if we always added the option? If the latter then the same method should work for those too.

